Resistance against its efforts or delaying the reforms could again cause a devastating attack on financial markets.
The Italian Federation of Foreign Banks exercises pressure with its indication that a failure is Montis a catastrophe.
Monti began on Monday with his debates with political parties, trade unions and entrepreneurships as well as with youth and women's organisations.
The session will be completed on Tuesday evening.
Monti was appointed this Sunday by Napolitano, who, in response to the crisis, launched an extremely rapid change of government.
After short breathing at the end of the last week, when it became known that Berlusconi would resign, due to the uncertainty about the success of the new Prime Minister, the costs for Italian government bonds have again reached critical limits.
Rescue Italy with a government debt of 1.8 billion euros would be too much for the current EU rescue screen.
